description:
&lt;p&gt;Shropshire Community Health NHS Trust provides a range of community-based health services for adults and children in Shropshire, Telford and Wrekin. We aim to provide high quality health services delivered wherever possible close to where people live - at home, in local clinics and at community hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recommended by colleagues as a place to work which is supported by the Trusts values to work as part of a team, being respectful, compassionate and professional. We are committed to investing in our workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following our recent CQC visit in 2019 the Trust received the overall rating as good.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a fantastic opportunity for you to join our motivated and dynamic Adult Community Services. The Locality Clinical Manager is responsible for the safe and effective delivery of a range of community services. This post is 1 of 6 localities across Shropshire, including Telford and Wrekin.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have a good understanding of leading, delivering and improving services in a changing system. You will be committed to high quality patient care, collaborate with our patients, families and carers and be committed to your own and others development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we will offer you continual professional and personal growth and the opportunity to work in a supportive leadership team reporting to the Head of Nursing and Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is suitable for candidates who are already qualified for the position and meeting the Person Specification, but also as a development opportunity for candidates looking to move into Operational Management. There would be support given by Operational Managers through using a ‘buddy’ system and mentoring. If you have the drive and ambition required for this position, please call to discuss further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact: Mandee Worrall, Head of Nursing and Operations (Adults) 07783258573.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Panel Interview: 16th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview Panel: 17th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
